MongoDB Atlas:

MongoDB Atlas provides an easy way to host and manage your data in the cloud. This tutorial guides you through creating an Atlas cluster, connecting to it, and loading sample data.

First Sign up MongoDB Atlas:
https://www.mongodb.com/cloud/atlas/register

(1)Signup using your own data or Google signup
(2)After Signup  first load sample data:
    Database -> click on 3 dots -> Load Sample Dataset

(3)Create new Database user:-

    Database Access -> Add New Database User

(4)Provide Network Access:-
    Network Access ->  ADD IP ADDRESS

(5)Connect Mongodb with Vscode:
    Database -> connect -> MongoDB for Vs Code[
            1. Install MongoDB for VS Code.
                In VS Code, open "Extensions" in the left navigation and search for "MongoDB for VS Code." Select the extension and click install.
            2. In VS Code, open the Command Palette.
                Click on "View" and open "Command Palette."
                Search "MongoDB: Connect" on the Command Palette and click on "Connect with Connection String."
            3. Connect to your MongoDB deployment.
                Paste your connection string into the Command Palette.
                    mongodb+srv://<username>:<password>@cluster0.4qym7yi.mongodb.net/

                    Replace <password> with the password for the <username> user.
                    When entering your password, make sure all special characters are URL encoded. 
            4. Click “Create New Playground” in MongoDB for VS Code to get started.
            ]

(6)Create API Key:
    Data API -> Create API Key
    

